# Loop run log

> Append-only log of every loop the foreman has executed.
> Phase 0 of each new loop greps this to reconcile token budgets and detect repeated patterns.
> Phase 6 of each completed loop appends one JSON entry.

---

## Format

Each entry is a JSON object on contiguous lines, preceded by a blank line.

```json
{
  "run_id": "[ISO timestamp, e.g., 2026-06-20T15:17:00Z]",
  "skill": "[loop name, e.g., email-loop / article-loop / code-review-loop]",
  "selection": "[topic or task identifier]",
  "phases_completed": [
    "state_init",
    "phase_1",
    "taste_phase_1_5",
    "phase_2_v1+v2",
    "phase_3_conservative+sharp",
    "critic_roundN",
    "archive"
  ],
  "iterations": [round count],
  "final_verdict": "[APPROVE / APPROVE_WITH_NOTES / HUMAN_OVERRIDE / OVER_BUDGET]",
  "draft_word_count": [N],
  "duration_minutes": [estimate],
  "tokens_estimate_this_run": "~[N]k",
  "escalations_to_human": [count],
  "auto_fixes_count": [total auto-fix count],
  "loop_compliance": {
    "iron_law_3_no_questions_to_user": true,
    "iron_law_5_skill_tool_explicit_invocation": true,
    "iron_law_5_1_continue_within_same_response": true,
    "taste_subagent_runs": [N],
    "verifier_isolation_correct": true
  }
}
```

---

## Why JSON and not free text

The log is consumed by:

1. **Phase 0** of each new loop — greps `tokens_estimate_this_run` to reconcile today's budget burn
2. **Periodic audit** — you'll want to look back at "what failed last week / what patterns repeat"
3. **Possible future analytics** — if you build any kind of "loop performance dashboard" later, structured data > free text

Append-only means: never edit an old entry. Wrong? Fine — write a new entry that corrects it.

